6. Discussion: The Demand-Side Misinterpretation

FAD correctly identifies a real tension:

If workers lose income, demand falls.

However, it incorrectly assumes:
	•	Labor disappears entirely
	•	Costs fall to zero universally
	•	Production remains frictionless

6.1 Corrected Model

In reality:
	•	Labor becomes more specialized
	•	Costs shift from wages → capital + maintenance + expertise
	•	Output remains constrained by:
	•	material limits
	•	error rates
	•	system fragility

6.2 Critical Insight

There is no such thing as “fully automated production”—only differently employed humans.

