7. The Myth of the $9,000 Omnipotent Robot

The Institute classifies the “$9,000 humanoid replacing all workers” claim as:

TLE (Technological Literalism Error)

Observed issues include:
	•	Task generalization failure
	•	Environment sensitivity
	•	Maintenance overhead exceeding acquisition cost
	•	Inability to handle edge cases (i.e., reality)

