8. Concluding Statement

This report definitively establishes that:
	•	Capitalism has not collapsed.
	•	Labor has not disappeared.
	•	Robots do not “do everything.”
	•	And no production system has ever run itself for longer than a lunch break.

At the same time, the Institute acknowledges that:

The global economy is indeed on the verge of total structural dissolution due to machines that both require constant human intervention and simultaneously eliminate all human roles.

These findings are mutually exclusive and therefore fully consistent with current economic discourse.

